
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Assignment 3</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" >
<link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="dizzy.ico">
</head>

<body>
<h1>HTML Guide</h1>

<div>
<h2>Common HTML Tags <span style="color:red">Outisde</span> of &lt;body&gt;</h2>
<p>Click <a href="index.html">here</a> to be directed to Homepage.</p>

<table style="width:100%;">

	<tr>
	<th style="width:30%;">Tag</th>
	<th style="width:35%;">Definition</th>
	<th style="width:35%;">Examples</th>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&gt;</td>
	<td>All HTML document must start with this tag and tells the browser what type of document to expect.</td>
	<td> <span style="color:lightblue">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span>
	<br>
	&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;head&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;title&gt;Example&lt;/title&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;/head&gt;
	
	</td>
	
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</td>
	<td>Used to identify the language of the text content on the web.</td>
	<td>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
	<br>
	<span style="color:lightblue">&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</span>
	<br>
	&lt;head&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;title&gt;Example&lt;/title&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;/head&gt;
	</td>
	
	</tr>
	
	
	<tr>
	<td>charset</td>
	<td>Used for displaying an HTML page correctly by letting the web browser know the character set used in the page.</td>
	<td>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;head&gt;
	<br>
	<span style="color:lightblue">&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;</span>
	<br>
	&lt;title&gt;Example&lt;/title&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;/head&gt;
	</td>
	
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>Title</td>
	<td>Used to define the title of the document and is shown in the browser's title bar or in the page's tab.</td>
	<td>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;head&gt;
	<br>
	meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
	<br>
	<span style="color:lightblue">&lt;title&gt;Example&lt;/title&gt;</span>
	<br>
	&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;/head&gt;</td>
	
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>Internal CSS</td>
	<td>Used to define a style for a single HTML page. Internal CSS is defined in the &lt;head&gt; section of an HTML page, within a &lt;style&gt; element.</td>
	<td>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;head&gt;
	<br>
	meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;title&gt;Example&lt;/title&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"&gt;
	<br>
	<span style="color:lightblue">&lt;style&gt;
	body {background-color: powderblue;}
	<br>
	h1   {color: blue;}
	<br>
	p    {color: red;}
	<br>
	&lt;/style&gt;</span>
	<br>
	&lt;/head&gt;</td>
	
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>External CSS</td>
	<td>A seperate CSS file that can change the look of an entire website by changing just one file.</td>
	<td>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;head&gt;
	<br>
	meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
	<br>
	&lt;title&gt;Example&lt;/title&gt;
	<br>
	<span style="color:lightblue">&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"&gt;</span>
	<br>
	(To access style.css file, press Ctrl + U while on website and click on <u><span style="color:blue">"style.css"</span></u> on line 6)
	<br>
	&lt;/head&gt;</td>
	
	</tr>
	
	
	<tr>
	<td>Faivcon</td>
	<td>A favicon is a small image that is displayed on the left of the page title in the browser tab.</td>
	<td><img src="s-l400.jpg" style="width:100px" alt="100 percent emoji">
	<p>This image that is shown ^above^ is next to the page title in the browser tab</p>
	<p>&lt;link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="dizzy.ico"&gt; </p></td>
	
	</tr>
	
</table>

</div>

</body>
</html>